Here's an example of how to set your Android activity to be displayed in full screen mode:

```
@Override
protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
    super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);

    // Set the activity to be full screen
    getWindow().setFlags(WindowManager.LayoutParams.FLAG_FULLSCREEN,
            WindowManager.LayoutParams.FLAG_FULLSCREEN);

    // Set the layout for the activity
    setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);
}
```

In this example, we're using the `getWindow()` method to get the current window and setting the `FLAG_FULLSCREEN` flag to make the activity go into full screen mode.

Note: If you want to hide the navigation bar as well, you can use the `View.SYSTEM_UI_FLAG_HIDE_NAVIGATION` flag on the root view of your activity.

If you're using the `AppCompatActivity` in your Android app and want to remove the title bar from your activity, you can do so by adding the following code to your `onCreate` method:

```
@Override
protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
    super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
    requestWindowFeature(Window.FEATURE_NO_TITLE);
    setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);
}
```

The `requestWindowFeature(Window.FEATURE_NO_TITLE)` will request to remove the title bar from your activity. 

Note that you need to call `requestWindowFeature` before `setContentView` in order for it to work properly.
